        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Touchette</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-07">July 7,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received July 7—9:18 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>262. ReContel 261, July 6. Martial law still in effect Peiping but situation
                    apparently easing following student demonstration July 5. Strict curfew imposed
                    night July 6 from 7 p. m., to 7 a. m. Curfew for night July 7 scheduled to be 11
                    p. m. to 6 p. m. [<hi rend="italic">a. m.?</hi>]</p>
                <p>Repeated Shanghai 276, Nanking 416, Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Touchette</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
